post_cb({"26216217": {"ParentId": "26210379", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>There's an implicit coversion from any non-pointer to member/member function to <code>void*</code>. After this is passed to the stream, it passes it off to <code>std::num_put::put()</code> which prints it out as a generic pointer as if by using the <code>\"%p\"</code> format flag.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "701092", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "26216217", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2014-10-06T12:26:59.130", "LastActivityDate": "2014-10-06T12:26:59.130"}, "26210379": {"CommentCount": "3", "ViewCount": "75", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "3747990", "CreationDate": "2014-10-06T05:20:29.133", "LastActivityDate": "2014-10-06T12:32:32.647", "LastEditDate": "2014-10-06T12:32:32.647", "AcceptedAnswerId": "26216217", "OwnerDisplayName": "user2953119", "Title": "Formatted output arithmetic inserters", "Id": "26210379", "Score": "0", "Body": "<p>I have a basic question about the arithmetic inserters; \u00a7 27.7.3.6.2/1  [ostream.inserters.arithmetic]:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_26210379_26210379_0\">When val is of type bool, long, unsigned long, long long, unsigned long long, double, long double, or const void*, the formatting conversion occurs as if it performed the following code fragment:</p>\n<pre><code>bool failed = use_facet&lt;\n  num_put&lt;charT,ostreambuf_iterator&lt;charT,traits&gt; &gt;\n    &gt; (getloc()).put(*this, *this, fill(), val).failed()\n</code></pre>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The question is what exact function performs the conversion from a pointer to type to, as Matt McNabb corrected, <code>const void*</code>? For instance:</p>\n<pre><code>int *ip = new int(1);\nstd::cout &lt;&lt; ip; //0xaa33fa67\n</code></pre>\n<p>I'm not concerned in an implementation details, I just would like to know what function produces arithmetic result from the pointer. Is it <code>put</code> in the example above?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><ostream>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_26210379_26210379_0": {"section_id": 2290, "quality": 1.0, "length": 24}}, "n3337": {"so_26210379_26210379_0": {"section_id": 2277, "quality": 1.0, "length": 24}}, "n4659": {"so_26210379_26210379_0": {"section_id": 2563, "quality": 1.0, "length": 24}}}});